areer-high 42 points and grabbed 14 rebounds in East Rutherford,N.J., to send Denver to its fourth straight loss, 138-110. . . . DarnellValentine scored nine of Cleveland's last 10 points and Danny Ferry scored 14in the fourth quarter to send New York to its seventh straight loss inRichfield, Ohio, 90-85. . . . Portland won its 11th straight at home, beatingUtah 117-105. . . . Benoit Benjamin had 27 points and 13 rebounds to help theClippers end a six-game losing streak with a 124-107 win over Minnesota in LosAngeles. . . . Host Dallas, which averaged 91.3 points in its previous sixgames, never trailed on the way to a 121-96 win over Washington.;  ETC.:Detroit signed guard John Long for the remainder of the season after his two10-day contracts expired. Long was signed to replace injured guard IsiahThomas on the roster. . . . The Miami Heat placed guard Jon Sundvold(pneumonia and a sinus inflammation) on the injured list and activated forwardTerry Davis.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News wire services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  SAN JOSE MERCURY NEWS  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910216  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Saturday  </DAY><MONTH>  February  </MONTH><PG.COL>  9D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  PHOTO  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  468  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Saturday February 16, 199100047193,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>